We should not make this change.
@zhangyanzhao asked me to make this change before and I did not think it is good idea to change it after this has been out like this misspelled for so many years.  Many community users may already adopt to this miss spelled word into their scripts and if we change this at this point, it will impact many of those automation scripts.
We should revert this change and just live with the way it is...

